, northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1078,1153,466,492]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. It deserves mentioning that field trips were conducted in this area some time ago (ca. 3 years ago), but the species was not found. Recently, there were no field trips in that area and, therefore, few samples of this species were analyzed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1382]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,488,582,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Habitat and ecology:—</emphasis>
Grows in “Carrasco” vegetation 
<typeStatus box="[869,922,582,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">type</typeStatus>
, at 
<quantity box="[963,1036,582,608]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" unit="m" value="760.0">760 m</quantity>
elevation. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Araujo, F. S. &amp; Martins, F. &amp; Shepherd, G. J." pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="663 - 678" refId="ref1737" refString="Araujo, F. S., Martins, F. R &amp; Shepherd, G. J. (1999) Variacoes estruturais e floristicas do carrasco no Planalto da Ibiapaba, Estado do Ceara. Revista Brasileira de Biologia 59: 663 - 678. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0034 - 71081999000400015" type="journal article" year="1999">Araújo et al. (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, the “Carrasco” is a dense, shruby and deciduous 
<typeStatus box="[869,920,621,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">type</typeStatus>
of vegetation, covering quartz-sandy soils, between altitudes of 700 and 
<quantity box="[499,576,660,686]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" unit="m" value="900.0">900 m</quantity>
, on the Ibiapaba and Araripe plateaus, in the Brazilian semiarid domain. The two collections, both with flowers, were gathered in November. The characteristics of fruits (drupes) are unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1382]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,488,776,802]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Conservation status:—</emphasis>
Considering that only two samples collected in the area during the study of the “Carrasco” vegetation (
<bibRefCitation author="Araujo, F. S. &amp; Martins, F. &amp; Shepherd, G. J." box="[424,637,814,840]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="663 - 678" refId="ref1737" refString="Araujo, F. S., Martins, F. R &amp; Shepherd, G. J. (1999) Variacoes estruturais e floristicas do carrasco no Planalto da Ibiapaba, Estado do Ceara. Revista Brasileira de Biologia 59: 663 - 678. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0034 - 71081999000400015" type="journal article" year="1999">Araújo et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
) and few individuals of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loiola" authorityYear="2013" box="[919,1200,813,839]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angelicae">
<emphasis box="[919,1200,813,839]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Erythroxylum angelicae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been observed at the site, this species was considered rare. However, based on 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN &amp; Cambridge, U. K." box="[904,1061,853,879]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" refId="ref1882" refString="IUCN (2001) The IUCN Red List categories and criteria, version 3.1. IUCN Species Survival Commission. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, U. K. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / technical-documents / categories-andcriteria / 2001 - categories-criteria (accessed 15 August 2013)." type="url" year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
criteria, the conservation status of this species is Data Deficient (DD).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1382]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,369,930,956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Discussion:—</emphasis>
In a preliminary list of 
<taxonomicName box="[644,896,929,956]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[644,804,929,955]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Erythroxylum</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
form 
<collectingRegion box="[970,1102,930,956]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Ceará state</collectingRegion>
, I identified both specimens of this new species as 
<taxonomicName authority="O. E. Schulz (1907: 42)" authorityName="O. E. Schulz" authorityPageNumber="42" authorityYear="1907" box="[410,993,968,995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laetevierens">
<emphasis box="[410,717,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Erythroxylum laetevierens</emphasis>
O.E. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schulz, O. E." box="[785,993,969,995]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref2426" refString="Schulz, O. E. (1907) Erythroxylaceae. In: Engler, A. (ed.) Das Pflanzenreich: regui vegetabilis conspectus. Verlag von H. R. Engelmann, Weinheim, pp. 1 - 176." type="book chapter" year="1907">Schulz (1907: 42)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
of section 
<taxonomicName box="[1122,1307,968,994]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Rhabdophyllum">
<emphasis box="[1122,1307,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Rhabdophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to the general aspect of the branches, leaf morphology, and geographical distribution (both species are sympatric). However, closed observations of this collections show that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loiola" authorityYear="2013" box="[900,1199,1045,1071]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angelicae">
<emphasis box="[900,1199,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Erythroxylum angelicae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to section 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. E. Schulz" authorityYear="1907" box="[151,362,1084,1110]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Archerythroxylum">
<emphasis box="[151,362,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Archerythroxylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on its non-striate stipules and triangular calyx lobes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1382]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loiola" authorityYear="2013" box="[198,480,1123,1149]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angelicae">
<emphasis box="[198,480,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Erythroxylum angelicae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially resembles several other species encountered in northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1357,1432,1124,1150]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Martius (1840: 387)" authorityName="Martius" authorityPageNumber="387" authorityYear="1840" box="[249,847,1162,1189]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vacciniifolium">
<emphasis box="[249,593,1162,1188]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Erythroxylum vacciniifolium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martius, K. F. P." box="[601,847,1163,1189]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="283 - 410" refId="ref2199" refString="Martius, K. F. P. (1840) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Planzengattung Erythroxylon. Abhandlungen der Mathematisch- Physikalischen Classe der Koniglich Bayerischen Akademie der Wissenschaften 3 (2): 283 - 410." type="journal article" year="1840">Martius (1840: 387)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, also of sect. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. E. Schulz" authorityYear="1907" box="[1014,1230,1162,1188]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Archerythroxylum">
<emphasis box="[1014,1230,1162,1188]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Archerythroxylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; differing by the length of setae (
<quantity box="[355,475,1201,1227]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1-1.5 mm</quantity>
long in 
<emphasis box="[582,781,1200,1226]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loiola" authorityYear="2013" box="[582,739,1200,1226]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angelicae">E. angelicae</taxonomicName>
vs.
</emphasis>
<quantity box="[792,935,1201,1227]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.6">0.6-0.8 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[979,1183,1200,1226]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vaccinifolium">
<emphasis box="[979,1183,1200,1226]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. vaccinifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), length of pedicels (inconspicuous, less 
<quantity box="[405,474,1240,1266]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long 
<emphasis box="[546,578,1240,1265]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">vs.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[587,675,1240,1266]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2-5mm</quantity>
) and shape of calyx lobes (triangular 
<emphasis box="[1140,1172,1240,1265]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">vs.</emphasis>
lanceolate). The new species is also similar, in general branching appearance and leaf morphology, to 
<taxonomicName authority="Plowman (1987: 35)" authorityName="Plowman" authorityPageNumber="35" authorityYear="1987" box="[1092,1436,1278,1304]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenue">
<emphasis box="[1092,1187,1278,1303]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. tenue</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Plowman, T. C." box="[1195,1436,1278,1304]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 41" refId="ref2331" refString="Plowman, T. C. (1987) Ten new species of Erythroxylum (Erythroxylaceae) from Bahia, Brazil. Fieldiana, Botany 19: 1 - 41." type="journal article" year="1987">Plowman (1987: 35)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
of sect. 
<emphasis box="[244,436,1316,1342]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Rhabdophhylum</emphasis>
; however, this last species have striated stipules. Other characters that distinguish 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loiola" authorityYear="2013" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angelicae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">E. angelicae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from these morphologically related species are presented in 
<tableCitation box="[977,1064,1356,1382]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,241,1433,1456]" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological comparison of Erythroxylum angelicae and its morphologically related species." pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
