<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1435,151,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName box="[151,419,151,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erytroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angelicae">
<emphasis box="[151,419,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Erytroxylum angelicae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the similar species discussed here are not found in sympatry. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1840" box="[1206,1408,151,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Erythroxylaceae" genus="Erythroxylum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vacciniifolium">
<emphasis box="[1206,1408,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">E. vacciniifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reported from savanna formations (cerrado) and savanna-steppe vegetation (caatinga) in the west-portion of 
